european central bank official says euro zone economy to recover soon
xinhua news agency , brussels , march 20 ( reporter wang xingqiao ) - the chief economist of the european central bank ( ecb ) , dr. yassin , said here on the 20 th that the euro zone 's economy has moved out of a low ebb , and this year it will begin to accelerate its recovery .
he made the above remarks at a hearing held by the european parliament in brussels .
he said the latest data show that the euro zone 's economy has been easing at the beginning of this year , and it is expected that the economic recovery rate will be accelerated within the year .
it is estimated that this year 's economic growth rate of the euro zone will reach 2 to 2.5 percent .
he said that the euro zone 's economic recovery was mainly attributable to the growth in consumer spending and the current commodity storage level of the euro zone has reached a very low level .
on inflation , he said that the overall economic growth rate of the euro zone has shown a downward trend , and there is no indication that there will be a risk of instability in prices in the medium - term period of economic development .
when talking about the current energy situation in the world , the imf said that the recent rise in the world oil market has caused concern among the economic decision - makers of various countries , and the impact of the oil price increase on the long - term economic trend should not be underestimated .
hong kong police detected first online drug trafficking
xinhua news agency , hong kong , march 21 , hong kong police recently found some people using the internet to engage in internet drug trafficking .
the narcotics division of the hong kong police force pointed out that this was the first time that the hong kong police had discovered that it should be taken seriously .
the hong kong police said that in the past year , a total of several drug cases were found in hong kong people using the internet to purchase ecstasy , such as the use of credit cards .
drug traffickers bought drugs in thailand and sent them to hong kong .
the chief superintendent of narcotics bureau of the hong kong police force , mr ip ka - chuen , pointed out that the number of cases detected last year were mainly used to order the internet by credit cards .
the hong kong police are working with the relevant disciplined services to crack down on this new crime .
at a recent cross - border symposium on cross - border organized crime in hong kong , a responsible official of the united nations international narcotics committee pointed out that drug trafficking on the internet would be a new challenge to law enforcement agencies in the future .
last year , the hong kong special administrative region security bureau completed consultation on computer - related crimes and amended legislation to combat any criminal activities using computers .
african university students call for not to be on the brink of new technology
xinhua news agency , abidjan , march 21 ( reporter song nan ) at the second african higher education forum , which opened on the 21 st , the university students attending the forum called on african youths to make active use of information and communications technology to cope with the challenges of economic globalization , and not to let the african continent become the " verge of new technology . "
in his speech , the chairman of the meeting held that new and high technologies have promoted the development of asian and european countries .
the arrival of the new century has brought many opportunities and challenges to the african continent , and african young people should strive to master new and high technologies and make their own contributions to the better future of africa .
the theme of the forum is : " new technology , information , and exchange will bring more opportunities to the african people . "
during the three - day meeting , experts from more than 10 institutions of higher learning and enterprises in africa will discuss the issues of " the future and new technological challenges of africa , " " cultural diversity and economic development , " and " opportunities and prospects of e - commerce for africa . "
a large - scale campus cultural exhibition will also be held during the conference .
indonesia reiterates opposition to foreign troops
xinhua news agency , jakarta , march 22 ( reporter ma tong ) - the indonesian foreign ministry issued a press communique on the 22 nd , reiterating opposition to foreign troops entering this island .
the indonesian foreign ministry reiterated this stand in response to a report in the " usa today " that the united states intends to send troops to indonesia to assist in cracking down on the " al - qaeda " members who had fled from afghanistan on 20 march .
the communique says that the us government has never formally raised the above demand to the indonesian government , and this can also be confirmed by the white house and the defense department later .
the communique reiterated that indonesia has pursued a proactive and independent foreign policy , and that indonesia has already conducted close and beneficial cooperation with the united states , and the indonesian government is willing to continue to strengthen cooperation in this regard .
