china united telecommunications corporation 's sales volume up nearly 38 percent last year
xinhua news agency report of march 27 from hong kong ( by staff reporter li kai ) - china united telecommunications corporation , which was listed on the hong kong stock exchange , announced here today that the total volume of business of china united telecommunications corporation reached 293.93 billion yuan in 2001 , and the total volume of sales reached 4.457 billion yuan , an increase of nearly 38 percent over the previous year .
as one of china 's comprehensive telecommunications operators , china unicom provides a variety of telecommunications services , including mobile telecommunications , international long - distance , data , internet , and paging services .
the china unicom announced that last year , the company 's long - distance telephone exchange and the total number of telephone business reached 64.1 billion minutes , an increase of 5.9 times over the previous year , and the market share has increased from 1.3% in 2000 to 7.7 percent , and the total international time for the whole year has increased by 3.4 times over the previous year .
yang xianzu , chief executive officer of the china united telecommunications corporation , said that this year , the company will continue to speed up the development of mobile telecommunications business , adopt a strategy of the same way , and ensure the coordinated development of the mobile communication business of the cdma and gongs and drums in the mobile telecommunications industry , so that the company 's mobile phone users will continue to grow by a large margin .
china , japan to sign agreement on exchange of currency
xinhua news agency , tokyo , march 28 ( reporter wang jizhen ) - - - - dai xianglong , governor of the people 's bank of china and governor of the bank of japan , signed a bilateral monetary exchange agreement between the renminbi and the japanese yen on the 28 th in tokyo .
according to the agreement , if necessary , the people 's bank of china and the bank of japan can provide each other with a total exchange of money equivalent to us $ 3 billion to help them maintain the stability of the financial market .
the signing of an agreement on exchange of money between china and japan shows that the cooperation between the central bank of china and japan has been further strengthened .
the agreement , signed between china and japan , is the second bilateral currency exchange agreement signed between the people 's bank of china and the bank of thailand in december 2001 .
in the future , china will also sign an agreement on exchange of currency with some countries such as the rok .
dai xianglong said : china will actively participate in asian financial cooperation , and is willing to work together with other asian countries and regions to make its own contributions to regional economic stability and prevention of risks .
wu dawei , chinese ambassador to japan , attended the signing ceremony of an agreement between the people 's bank of china and the bank of japan on the exchange of currencies .
earthquake victims in afghanistan hit home
xinhua news agency , kabul , march 28 ( reporter pan yunzhao ) - the earthquake victims in the northern afghanistan province of baghdad have started their work to rebuild their homes for three days .
a spokesman for the united nations office for humanitarian aid in afghanistan said to xinhua reporters that a central group , composed of the afghan interim government , un organizations , and non - governmental organizations , was conducting an inspection and assessment of the earthquake - stricken areas on the 28 th , and found that the disaster victims had already started the reconstruction of their own houses , and some of them had used relief organizations to provide relief materials to the disaster victims .
in view of this situation , the un rescue organization has started to consider the issue of helping disaster victims rebuild their homes , she said .
at present , rescue organizations have already had a large amount of relief supplies in the quake - hit areas , and are making use of ground and air - to - air means to provide disaster victims .
a strong earthquake occurred on the 25 th in the area of the afghan province of najaf province , killing and injuring tens of thousands of people .
