computer crime inflicted losses of billions of us dollars last year
xinhua news agency , washington , april 7 , the " 2001 computer crime and security investigation report " published by the united states on the 7 th showed that the increasingly brazen computer crime last year caused a loss of several billion us dollars to us companies and government departments , a big increase over 2000 .
the computer systems in all parts of the united states have been attacked by computer viruses , refused service attacks , and all kinds of security loopholes .
a total of 538 computer security experts from enterprises , government departments , and universities said that us companies and other institutions are required to pay a high price for computer - related crimes every year .
although the exact amount of losses was not yet final , 35 percent of the investigation departments admitted that they had suffered losses , with a total amount of more than $ 37.7 billion , a significant increase of nearly $ 26.56 billion over the year 2000 .
the report jointly compiled by the us computer security association and the federal bureau of investigation did not provide an assessment of the loss of personal users throughout the country .
