taiwan democratic progressive party legislator chen jinde visits beijing
chen jinde , a member of the taiwan democratic progressive party , arrived in beijing yesterday for a visit to beijing with a number of taiwan fishery groups .
chen jinde was the first member of the democratic progressive party to visit the mainland after the chinese vice premier qian qichen delivered a speech on the 7 th anniversary of " jiang 's eight - point proposal " to welcome the visit of the vast number of dpp members to the mainland in a proper capacity .
chen jinde arrived in hong kong on saturday for a 10 - day visit .
chen jinde stressed that the purpose of his visit was to help him solve the problem of the shortage of fishing industry in the yilan district . he did not want to visit the mainland in his personal capacity . however , he revealed that he would meet with the chinese ministry of foreign trade and economic cooperation and the mainland 's relevant non - governmental organizations , and hoped that the beijing authorities would agree to resume the opening of the fishing industry .
after the chinese mainland prohibits the fishing industry from entering taiwan , the fishing industry in the yilan area is seriously inadequate , and because of the help of the fishing industry in the electoral district , chen jinde decided to visit beijing and taiwan 's fishing industry association , and help the industry in the mainland to resume the opening of fishing industry and the fishing industry .
the delegation was formed by the chairman of the 13 regional fishing association of taiwan province , led by huang yongjia , director - general of the taiwan provincial fisheries association , and headed a delegation to beijing on thursday in the name of the " republic of china employment union . "
another serious sandstorms occurred in beijing
( beijing , new law ) chinese media said that serious sandstorms occurred in beijing yesterday .
although the government has invested a huge amount of money to improve the environment in beijing and prevent the desert from approaching beijing , the main difficulties facing beijing 's bid to host the 2008 olympic games are still the most difficult .
china 's state meteorological bureau forecast that the first sandstorms hit beijing last friday , and the cold air in mongolia is expected to be overshadowed by beijing in the sand dust .
yang weixi , chief engineer of the chinese ministry of forestry 's desert control center , told the beijing zhou bao : " i dare not say that there will be no sandstorms in 2008 . "
what we can do is to control the artificial factors of sand storms and prevent desertification . "
he said , however , these natural factors , such as wind , drought , and big desert , have caused china to avoid sand storms in the short term .
the chinese government has promised to invest 56.8 billion yuan ( about 12.3 billion new taiwan dollars ) in 2002 to prevent desertification and to reduce sand storms .
beijing alone spent about 1 billion yuan ( about 200 million new taiwan dollars ) this year .
an expert from the chinese academy of forestry said : " the increase in fiscal funding will greatly improve the situation , but it may take several decades to see the results of the management . "
after a survey conducted early this year , chinese environmental experts warned : about one - third of china 's territory is now a desert , which is mainly caused by human economic activities , such as the overlay .
the investigation report said that in the first six months of last year , 18 sandstorms occurred in beijing , and the sand comes from inner mongolia and 60 percent of inner mongolia 's land was the desert .
at the just - concluded npc session this month , the npc deputies from shanghai , beijing , and inner mongolia urged the government to " establish a green great wall ( composed of forests ) " to stop sand storms .
according to the " shanghai star " report , xu shiyuan , vice president of the china institute of geography , warned that if the government does not take emergency measures , the sandstorms may even hit shanghai .
many of china 's cadres who have been hit by false diplomas have been verified
a few days ago , the graduate employment guidance center of the guangdong provincial higher educational institution , which was hit by a false certificate in the pan - pearl river delta ( hong kong ) , was confirmed to have 15 officials in a certain city in the chaoshan region , and only seven of them were false certificates .
the hong kong newspaper reported that since may last year , the center has received more than 3,500 certificates of the certificate and more than 800 certificates of various kinds , and the rate of false certificates is as high as 23 percent .
the report said that these false certificates were mostly printed on adult education and self - examination certificates , two - thirds of which were forged on the street , and one - third were issued by regular educational institutions .
the person in charge of the center also disclosed that , since the establishment of the ministry of investigation and the system is being carried out at the same time , the majority of the institutions and enterprises , including some units that have a very high percentage of forged documents , and many of the owner of false certificates are working cadres .
with the approval of the relevant departments of the ministry of education , the employment guidance center for the graduates of guangdong province is the only institution in china that has been authorized to carry out a national certificate of higher education examination .
the responsible person also disclosed that the state - owned banks in a prefecture - level city , out of consideration of the selection of officials , have submitted a certificate of the 36 middle - level officials and the backbone of the business , and only six are true .
it has been learned that as the appraisal is carried out , many private enterprises are also required to make assessment , and the main items they have identified are those who should be hired and new students .
the identification department found that many of the university students ' certificates were fake goods .
last year , a large enterprise set up a branch in a certain area in the pearl river delta region , and recruited a number of university students .
the boss sent more than 30 certificates of academic credentials to the staff and found out that 10 of them were false .
in recent years , many foreign - funded institutions have set up separate teaching points in guangdong province , and they do not have the qualification to issue a certificate of academic credentials . however , in order to attract students to apply for admission , they have been able to issue a batch of false certificates to the students .
25 seeking asylum for korean people arrive in seoul
( seoul , aug. 25 ) twenty - five korean people seeking asylum arrived at seoul international airport yesterday to begin a new life in south korea .
after passing the test , they waved their hands to korean tv cameras .
at a temporary press conference held at the airport , the 43 - year - old factory worker li song - song said : " we hope to settle here and live in a free world of hope . "
another man said : " because south korea is a free country , i will not hesitate to die this . "
on thursday , these people intruding into the chinese embassy in beijing , firmly indicating they would take to the rok .
china on friday allowed them to travel to seoul via the philippines .
they came from six families , of which two girls did not have parents .
they are the group with the largest number of people who have fled since the end of the korean war .
according to the south korean national intelligence agency , the group will join the 2,000 north korean people settled in south korea , of which 138 will only seek refuge this year .
last year , 583 people went to the rok to break the record .
the new 25 people will be able to adapt themselves to a government reception near the capital of seoul .
the primary objective of the course is to help the movement to overcome the tense situation of escape , and to receive counselling , adapt to the korean culture , including the capitalist world 's understanding .
the final step is to receive new work training .
