on - street crimes increase in britain
( london , united states ) the british government is committed to tackling the increasingly serious street crime and will send more police officers to patrol .
the secretary of home affairs brundtland said that it is very necessary to stop on - street robberies and violence , and to strengthen police patrol .
he said : " we should truly straighten out the order on the streets , because the law - abiding citizens hope to be safe on the streets , and they will not be afraid that they will be attacked . "
despite the drop in the overall crime rate in britain , the number of on - street crimes increased by 13 percent from 2000 to 2001 .
the situation in london was even more shocking , and the number of robbery cases reported in september and november 2001 was 9.48 million , an increase of more than doubled over the same period of the previous year .
the government also said that the increase in crime was mainly due to a large increase in the number of mobile phones , and more than 700,000 mobile phone robberies occurred last year .
this is the first time that the british police have placed the focus of their crackdown on street hooligans and robbers , and they have been concentrating on cracking down on illegal buying and selling of drugs on the streets .
the new plan will first be implemented in 10 streets - related crimes cases .
police will step up patrol in these streets and provide more protection to victims .
